- "Most recent versions" refers to the top 3 versions based on the creation date;
- "First feature" and "first parameter" refer to the features and parameters with the lowest IDs for each processor;
- "Version number starting with '2.'" indicates a specific range of versions.

- Critical features are those with more than one parameter, at least one of which is configurable;
- Configurable parameters are those that can be modified by users;
- Administrators are users with the role 'admin';
- The query focuses on actions where the parameter values were updated.

- "touched by the hands of the engineers" refers to actions performed by users with the role 'engineer';
- "leaving behind the marks of their updates" refers to actions of type 'update';
- "recently" implies the most recent action for each version and parameter, as determined by the action timestamp.

- 'High' frequency is defined as more than 10 actions;
- 'Medium' frequency is defined as between 5 and 10 actions;
- 'Low' frequency is defined as 5 or fewer actions.

- "Bloom" refers to a processor;
- "Petals" refer to features of a processor;
- "Branches" refer to distinct parameters of a feature;
- "Leaves" refer to distinct configurations (values) of a parameter.

- Critical features are those marked as essential for system operation;
- 'Reset' features are specific functions that can reset the processor;
- Integer parameters are parameters with a VHDL type of 'integer';
- The most recent version of a processor is determined by the latest creation date.

- "values above 10" refers to parameter values that exceed 10;
- "average parameter value" is calculated by converting the parameter values to real numbers and averaging them;
- "overall average" is the average of all parameter values across all processors.

- 'processor_id = 1' refers to a specific processor in the system;
- 'parameter_out_of_range' is a specific parameter that triggers alerts;
- The 'version_level' in the VersionHistory CTE indicates the hierarchical level of the version in the versioning system.

- 'Processors blooming between the dawn of 2020 and the twilight of 2025' refers to processors released between January 1, 2020, and December 31, 2025;
- 'Equipped with the power management features' refers to features in the 'power management' category;
- 'Seen more than two updates pruned from their branches' refers to having more than 2 update actions.

- "blessed by an engineer" refers to versions approved by a user with the role 'engineer';
- "unveiled in the recent quintet of years" refers to processors released within the last 5 years;
- The role 'engineer' is associated with the permission to modify configurations, indicated by the JSON string containing `"modify_config": true`.

- "Parameter values" are specific settings or configurations in the system;
- "Alerts" are notifications or warnings generated by the system when certain conditions are met;
- "Percentage" is calculated by dividing the number of unique parameter values with alerts by the total number of parameter values, then multiplying by 100.

- "logarithm base-2 of parameter values > 1" refers to parameter values that have doubled at least once;
- "version created more than 30 days ago" means the version was created over a month ago;
- "more than 2 actions performed" indicates that the version has seen more than two interactions or modifications.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM processors 
WHERE release_date < '2022-01-01' AND end_of_life > '2030-01-01';
